Export and import data fixtures for app development.

Fixtures are JSON files loaded during app installation to provide
default data like roles, workflows, print formats, etc.

Examples:
  weg fixtures export myapp              # Export all fixtures
  weg fixtures export myapp --doctype Role
  weg fixtures import myapp              # Import fixtures
  weg fixtures list myapp                # List fixture files

Usage:
  weg fixtures [command]

Available Commands:
  export      Export fixtures for an app
  import      Import fixtures for an app
  list        List fixture files for an app

Flags:
  -h, --help   help for fixtures

Global Flags:
  -C, --chdir string              Run as if weg was started in <path>
      --config string             Path to config file (default: auto-detect)
      --debug-categories string   Filter debug output: all,config,state,net,git,fs,exec
      --log-level string          Set log level: quiet, normal, verbose, debug, trace
  -o, --output string             Output format: auto, json, table, plain, quiet (default "auto")
  -q, --quiet                     Suppress non-essential output
  -v, --verbose count             Increase verbosity (-v, -vv, -vvv)
  -y, --yes                       Assume yes for all prompts

Use "weg fixtures [command] --help" for more information about a command.
